{% set active_section_key = section_key | default(value="section_1_required_data_layer") %}
{% set active_total_chapters = total_chapters | default(value="20") %}
{% set template_path = "story-dossier-worksheet-template.sections.md" %}
{% set worksheet_template = template_path | doc %}
{% set section_start = "[" ~ active_section_key ~ "]" %}
{% set section_end = "[/" ~ active_section_key ~ "]" %}
{% set target_section_shell = worksheet_template | extract_section(start=section_start, end=section_end) | trim %}

You are completing exactly one section of a cascading story dossier for Diamond Prompt Runner.

Your job is to fill only the target section and return it in parseable wrapped form so it can be appended to `story-dossier.md`.

Rules:

- Complete only the target section shown below.
- Keep the heading `## {{ active_section_key }}` exactly.
- Preserve the internal markdown structure of the section shell.
- Preserve any existing bracket wrappers inside the section shell exactly as given.
- Return the target section with all existing nested bracket wrappers preserved exactly.
- Do not remove, rename, reorder, or flatten any inner wrappers such as subsection containers, chapter containers, or structure containers.
- Fill bracketed fields and follow bracketed directions inside the target section, then remove those bracketed instructions from the final text.
- Do not rewrite or recap prior sections.
- Be decisive. Do not provide multiple options in the final output.
- Respect the target chapter count.
- Treat all named entities and explicit facts in the author seed and completed dossier as canon.
- Do not rename characters, change surnames, change roles, change family relationships, or change the core setup unless the upstream canon explicitly says to do so.
- If the target section text refers to `brain_dump` and this is not section 1, interpret that as the author seed information preserved below and in the completed dossier so far.
- If the author seed and your inference conflict, the author seed wins.
- If the completed dossier so far and your inference conflict, the completed dossier so far wins.
- Preserve these anchor facts exactly unless upstream canon explicitly changes them:
  - Klaus Schumann is the driver.
  - Marianna "Anna" Pisano is Vittorio Pisano's niece.
  - She first appears anonymously, then reappears as his assigned intern.
  - The romance unfolds across three back-to-back race weekends.
- Return only one wrapped section. No prefacing, no commentary, no code fences.

